Russia Equity Movers: AvtoVAZ, Novatek, Rosneft Shares Trade

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-07-20T15:54:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/russia-equity-movers-avtovaz-novatek-lukoil-rosneft.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  increased
0.07 percent to 1,701.37 at the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, after
earlier advancing as much as 1 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index gained 0.5 percent to 1,936.54.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO  AvtoVAZ (AVAZ)   gained 1.8 percent to 31.847 rubles,
the highest closing level since Feb. 3, after Interfax cited
Chief Executive Officer Igor Komorov as saying the Russian
carmaker may report a first-half profit of 2 billion rubles ($71
million).  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),  Russia ’s biggest crude producer,
rose for a second day, adding 1.1 percent to 234.51 rubles. Oil
futures gained as much as $1.52 in  New York .  OAO Novatek (NOTK RX), Russia’s largest private natural-gas
producer, climbed the most since July 1, rising 2.5 percent to
378.24 rubles after Vedomosti reported that the company is
interested in buying 51 percent of OAO Gazprom’s Nortgaz unit,
citing Novatek Chief Executive Officer Leonid Mikhelson.  -- Editors: Linda Shen, John Kohut  To contact the reporter on this story:
